The paper deals with the problem of building robust fuzzy extractors, which is a cryptographic primitive. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in its analysis of the security and efficiency of the proposed fuzzy extractor. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning (cs.LG) and computer engineering (cs.CE) in its discussion of biometric authentication and key recovery.
